Service Section 3: Retaining Walls
Suggested H2: Retaining Walls Barrie & Simcoe County — Armour Stone, Block, Concrete & Engineered Solutions
Body Copy Block:
A retaining wall does two jobs: it holds back earth and it makes a statement. At [Company Name], we design and build retaining walls that do both beautifully — from natural armour stone walls that blend seamlessly into rural and lakeside landscapes, to precision-engineered block systems suited to residential grade changes and commercial applications.
Every retaining wall we build includes proper drainage behind the wall — because without drainage, even the most well-built wall will eventually fail. We size our walls correctly, prepare our base properly, and install crushed stone drainage backfill and weep holes as standard practice.
Retaining Wall Types — Sub-Section Copy Blocks:
Armour Stone:
Armour stone retaining walls are among the most durable and visually striking options available in Central Ontario. Each large natural limestone or granite stone is set precisely to lock the wall together without mortar, distributing load evenly and allowing natural drainage through the face. The result is a wall that won't shift, won't sag, and looks better year after year — ideal for lakeside properties, rural estates, sloped driveways, and high-end residential projects.
Segmental Block:
Segmental concrete block retaining walls (brands like Unilock, Risi, Allan Block) offer versatility, clean modern lines, and engineered load ratings for walls up to and beyond 1.2 metres. Ideal for residential grade separations, garden terracing, and commercial applications where a uniform, refined appearance is desired.
Concrete:
Poured concrete and precast concrete retaining walls offer exceptional strength for high-load or high-height applications. When a site demands maximum structural performance — steep slopes, heavy surcharge loads, proximity to structures — concrete is often the engineered solution of choice.
Engineered Solutions:
For walls exceeding standard height thresholds, walls supporting structures, or sites with complex loading conditions, our team coordinates engineered retaining wall designs including geogrid-reinforced earth systems, sheet pile solutions, and stamped engineer-approved drawings to meet Ontario Building Code requirements.

